  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "1.1Systems are available to provide inclusive education services to children with disabilities and most vulnerable children in and out of school1.2 Personalized services are received by children with disabilities (including those with most complex disabilities) and their families from local government and non-government service providers in both home and school settings.2.1 Inclusive education stakeholders have the capacity to accommodate the diverse needs of all children and children with disabilities also reducing stigma and discrimination2.2 Parents and schools are engaged to demonstrate knowledge and skills on models and approaches for inclusive education.3.1 Good practices and lessons on inclusive education are identified, collected and disseminated for future scaling up and replication (using Making it Work approach)"
    },
